As we can see in the results above:

  • Pas, Bolsa de valores and Praa Principal have only one possible value, and as such give no insight to any kind of information for the aggregate of companies.
In[74]:
df.drop(columns= {'Pas', 'Praa Principal', 'Bolsa de valores'}, inplace=True)

Nmero de Empregados ltimo ano dsp. also has some non-numeric values (n.a), which makes it bad to parse down road. As such, since the number of employees cannot be negative in real life, it can be set to -1 as a convention to indicate bad data:

In[75]:
df = df.drop(df.loc[df['Nmero de Empregados ltimo ano dsp.']== 'n.a.', 'Nmero de Empregados ltimo ano dsp.'].index)
df['Nmero de Empregados ltimo ano dsp.'] = df['Nmero de Empregados ltimo ano dsp.'].astype('int16')

There are also some companies which have no operatinonal results in the latest year, and as such can be discarded from the dataframe:

In[76]:

Step 5: Adding information

Put economy sectors in a new column via the NACE code to group them in the future

In[79]:
'''
The first two digits of the NACE code give us what sector the company works in:
    01-03 Setor primrio
    05-43 Setor secundrio
    45-99 Setor tercirio
'''

setor_codigo = { (1, 3) : 'Primrio',
                 (5, 43) : 'Secundrio',
                 (45, 99) : 'Tercirio' }

df['Setor'] = pd.Series(dtype=pd.StringDtype())

# Verify that the column is in the dataframe
print(df.columns[-1])

# Give the correct value for the Setor column, in 
for index in range(0, df.shape[0]):
    for intervalo, setor in setor_codigo.items():
        if intervalo[0] <= df.at[index, 'Cdigo da NACE Rev. 2 Primria'] // 100 <= intervalo[1]:
            df.at[index, 'Setor'] = setor
            break

Setor

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as mtick
import numpy as np

default_fig_name = "figures/Figure_"
fig_num = 1

def autolabel(rects):
    for rect in rects:
        h = rect.get_height()
        ax.text((rect.get_x()+rect.get_width()/2), 1.02*h, h.round(2),
                ha='center', va='bottom')

sect_df = df[['Setor', 'Proveitos Operacionais mil EUR ltimo ano dsp.']]
total = df['Proveitos Operacionais mil EUR ltimo ano dsp.'].sum()
sect_df = sect_df.groupby('Setor', as_index=False).sum()

fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(7, 5))

x = np.arange(sect_df.shape[0])

y = (df['Setor'].value_counts().sort_values() / len(df['Setor'])) * 100
rects1 = ax.bar(x-0.15, y, width= 0.3, label = 'Setor')

y =  (sect_df['Proveitos Operacionais mil EUR ltimo ano dsp.'] / total) * 100
rects2 = ax.bar(x+0.15, y, width= 0.3, label = 'Setor')

ax.set_ylabel('% do total')
ax.set_xlabel('Setor')
ax.set_title('Diviso de empresas e volume de negcios, mil EUR (2023), por setor')
ax.set_xticks(x)
ax.set_xticklabels(sect_df['Setor'])
ax.legend((rects1[0], rects2[0]), ('% volume de negcios', '% empresas'))
ax.margins(y=0.2)
autolabel(rects1)
autolabel(rects2)

plt.savefig(default_fig_name + str(fig_num) + '.svg', bbox_inches='tight', format="svg")
fig_num += 1
plt.show()

def autolabel(rects, index):
    for rect in rects:
        w = rect.get_width()
        h = rect.get_height()
        ax.text(rect.get_x()+w, (1+(0.02*index))*h, h.round(2), ha='center', va='bottom', rotation=60)
        
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 6))

ind = np.arange(len(df_emp_loc['Localidade']))

rects1 = ax.bar(ind, rel_prov, 0.4, color='C0')
rects2 = ax.bar(ind+0.4, rel_empr, 0.4, color='C1')

ax.set_xlabel('Localidade')
ax.set_ylabel('% do total')
ax.set_title("Relao entre volume de negcios e empregados, % do total")
ax.margins(y=0.15)
ax.set_xticks(ind+0.2)
ax.set_xticklabels(df_emp_loc['Localidade'], rotation=60)
ax.legend((rects1[0], rects2[0]), ('% volume de negcios', '% empregados'))

autolabel(rects1, 0)
autolabel(rects2, 1)

# Source: https://ec.europa.eu/eurostat/web/products-manuals-and-guidelines/-/ks-ra-07-015
# Validating the NACE codes file, if it isn't valid it will throw a ValueError

with open('nace_codes.txt') as f:
    line_number = 0
    line = f.readline()
    while line:
        words = line.split(' ')
        if not(words[0][0] == 'S' or str.isdigit(words[0][0]) or words[0][0] == '\n'):
            print('line didnt start with S for section or number for code')
            print('character: ', words[0][0], 'line number: ', line_number)
            raise ValueError('Invalid start of line, either is "S" or a digit')
        line = f.readline()
        line_number += 1

    f.close()

print("File is valid.")

File is valid.

df_code = pd.DataFrame()

df_code['Code'] = pd.Series(dtype=pd.Int16Dtype())
df_code['Description'] = pd.Series(dtype=pd.StringDtype())

with open('nace_codes.txt') as f:
    line = f.readline()
    while line:
        words = line.split(' ')
        if str.isdigit(words[0]) and len(words[0]) == 2:
            df_code.loc[len(df_code.index)] = [int(words[0]), line[len(words[0]):]]
        line = f.readline()

df_code['Count'] = pd.Series(data=np.zeros(df.shape[0]),dtype=pd.Int16Dtype())
